mp7002MIBversion.name: mp7002MIBversion
mp7002MIBversion.description: Identifies the version of the MIB. The format of the version is x.yzT, where 'x' identifies the major revision number, 'y' identifies the minor revision number, 'z' identifies the typographical revision, and T identifies the test revision. Acceptable values for the individual revision components are as follows: x: 1 - 9 y: 0 - 9 z: 0 - 9 T: A - Z Upon formal release, no designation for the test revision will be present.

mp7002VersionEntry.name: mp7002VersionEntry
mp7002VersionEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Mp7002System Version Table.

mp7002VersionIndex.name: mp7002VersionIndex
mp7002VersionIndex.description: This object identifies Version parameters associated with the managed object.

mp7002FirmwareRev.name: mp7002FirmwareRev
mp7002FirmwareRev.description: The version number of the firmware, to allow products to know which revision is installed. The released version number is sequenced from --, A-, ... AA, ... ZZ. Test versions are numerical from 01 to 99.

mp7002ModelNumber.name: mp7002ModelNumber
mp7002ModelNumber.description: This variable is used to determine the type of card family installed ex. MP7002.

mp7002E1x.name: mp7002E1x
mp7002E1x.description: Indicates if the E1X Cascade Interface is installed.

mp7002MaintenanceTable.name: mp7002MaintenanceTable
mp7002MaintenanceTable.description: The table describes the maintenance objects for the unit and references the unit interface (cc = 00).

mp7002MaintenanceEntry.name: mp7002MaintenanceEntry
mp7002MaintenanceEntry.description: An entry in the GDC E1 Maintenance Table.

mp7002MaintenanceLineIndex.name: mp7002MaintenanceLineIndex
mp7002MaintenanceLineIndex.description: This object identifies Maintenance parameters associated with the managed object.

mp7002SoftReset.name: mp7002SoftReset
mp7002SoftReset.description: Supports the action of soft resetting the unit. When this object is set to reset(2), then the unit performs a soft reset, whose meaning is specific to the type of unit being managed. The value of norm(1) will be returned when the reset is complete. The value of norm(1) can not be set by management.

mp7002SysUpTime.name: mp7002SysUpTime
mp7002SysUpTime.description: This variable is used to report the elapsed system tick time for conversion to real time at the controller and is not related to the sysUpTime referenced in MIB-II. Upon power-up of the unit, the elapsed time is cleared. The elapsed time counter rolls over upon reaching the maximum count.

mp7002DefaultInit.name: mp7002DefaultInit
mp7002DefaultInit.description: This is used to allow the NonVolatile Configuration to be set to a factory default state. When this value is set to factoryDefault(1) the unit will perform a reset to make the default configuration take affect. The value of normal(2) will be returned when the initialization is complete. The value of normal(2) can not be set by management.

mp7002ResetStats.name: mp7002ResetStats
mp7002ResetStats.description: Supports the action of soft resetting the mp7002NearEndValidIntervals object. When this object is set to reset(2), then the unit will reset the mp7002NearEndValidIntervals object to zero. The value of norm(1) can not be set by management.

mp7002LedStatus.name: mp7002LedStatus
mp7002LedStatus.description: Returns a bitwise snapshot of the front panel LED state. Octet 1 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - ON bit 5 - INSV bit 4 - RSP bit 3 - TMG bit 2 - NIU bit 1 - D_I bit 0 - future use Octet 2 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - future use bit 5 - NTWK AIS bit 4 - NTWK LCV bit 3 - NTWK LOS bit 2 - NTWK OOF bit 1 - ALM bit 0 - TM Octet 3 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - ST- future use bit 5 - LT- future use bit 4 - RL- future use bit 3 - future use bit 2 - future use bit 1 - future use bit 0 - future use

mp7002E1Circuit.name: mp7002E1Circuit
mp7002E1Circuit.description: Circuit name E1 is connected to.

mp7002E1XCircuit.name: mp7002E1XCircuit
mp7002E1XCircuit.description: Circuit Name E1X is connected to

mp7002TSBundle1Name.name: mp7002TSBundle1Name
mp7002TSBundle1Name.description: Name first Time Slot Bundle is assigned to. Only used when unit is configured for drop side interface

mp7002TSBundle2Name.name: mp7002TSBundle2Name
mp7002TSBundle2Name.description: Name second Time Slot Bundle is assigned to. Only used when unit is configured for drop side interface.

mp7002SetRealTime.name: mp7002SetRealTime
mp7002SetRealTime.description: Number of seconds from midnight Dec 31, 1969.

mp7002AlarmStatus.name: mp7002AlarmStatus
mp7002AlarmStatus.description: Returns a bit-wise Status of alarms Octet 1 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - NWTK_LOS bit 5 - NWTK_LOF bit 4 - NWTK_AIS bit 3 - NTWK_LCV bit 2 - TIMING LOSS bit 1 - NTWK_NE_ES bit 0 - NTWK_NE_BBE Octet 2 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - NTWK_NE_SES bit 5 - NTWK_NE_UAS bit 4 - NTWK_FE_ES bit 3 - NTWK_FE_BBE bit 2 - NTWK_FE_SES bit 1 - NTWK_FE_UAS bit 0 - NTWK_RAI Octet 3 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - E1X_LOS bit 5 - E1X_LOF bit 4 - E1X_AIS bit 3 - E1X_NE_ES bit 2 - E1X_NE_BBE bit 1 - E1X_NE_SES bit 0 - E1X_NE_UAS Octet 4 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - E1X_FE_ES bit 5 - E1X_FE_BBE bit 4 - E1X_FE_SES bit 3 - E1X_FE_UAS bit 2 - NVRAM corrupted bit 1 - unit failure bit 0 - Power-up Alarm

mp7002SystemTimingGenStatus.name: mp7002SystemTimingGenStatus
mp7002SystemTimingGenStatus.description: Indicates if the units configured for primary or secondary system clock are actually supplying clock and if it is the 8hkz, 4mhz, or both.

mp7002FarEndResetStats.name: mp7002FarEndResetStats
mp7002FarEndResetStats.description: Supports the action of soft resetting the mp7002FarEndValidIntervals object. When this object is set to reset(2), then the unit will reset the mp7002FarEndValidIntervals object to zero. The value of norm(1) can not be set by management.

mp7002NearEndStatLastInitialized.name: mp7002NearEndStatLastInitialized
mp7002NearEndStatLastInitialized.description: Number of seconds from midnight Dec 31, 1969 up until mp7002NearEndValidIntervals was last initialized to zero

mp7002FarEndStatLastInitialized.name: mp7002FarEndStatLastInitialized
mp7002FarEndStatLastInitialized.description: Number of seconds from midnight Dec 31, 1969 up until mp7002FarEndValidIntervals was last initialized to zero

mp7002ConfigEntry.name: mp7002ConfigEntry
mp7002ConfigEntry.description: The GDC E1 Configuration table entry.

mp7002ConfigIndex.name: mp7002ConfigIndex
mp7002ConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002InterfaceType.name: mp7002InterfaceType
mp7002InterfaceType.description: The operating mode of the interface to be either Network Side, Drop Side or not assigned.

mp7002RcvrRange.name: mp7002RcvrRange
mp7002RcvrRange.description: Sets the receiver range to short (6dB) or long (36dB)

mp7002FallbackClockSource.name: mp7002FallbackClockSource
mp7002FallbackClockSource.description: Identifies the fallback transmit clock source.

mp7002NearEndValidIntervals.name: mp7002NearEndValidIntervals
mp7002NearEndValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 16 unless the interface was brought on-line within the last 4 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals the since interface has been online. This object is only valid for the E1 interface.

mp7002FarEndValidIntervals.name: mp7002FarEndValidIntervals
mp7002FarEndValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 16 unless the interface was brought on-line within the last 4 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals the since interface has been online. This object is only valid for the E1 interface.

mp7002NetworkConnection.name: mp7002NetworkConnection
mp7002NetworkConnection.description: Sets whether the network interface is standby or online. This only applies to the Network Interface.

mp7002Framing.name: mp7002Framing
mp7002Framing.description: Set the framing for the interface. Abbreviations are as follows: CCS - common-channel signaling PCS0 - per channel signaling phase 0 PCS1 - per channel signaling phase 1

mp7002LineCoding.name: mp7002LineCoding
mp7002LineCoding.description: Sets the line coding for the interface.

mp7002SysTimingTable.name: mp7002SysTimingTable
mp7002SysTimingTable.description: The GDC System Timing table. These are unit options at the system level.

mp7002SysTimingEntry.name: mp7002SysTimingEntry
mp7002SysTimingEntry.description: The GDC E1 Configuration table entry.

mp7002SysTimingIndex.name: mp7002SysTimingIndex
mp7002SysTimingIndex.description: Index value into the system configuration table.

mp7002SysTimingGen.name: mp7002SysTimingGen
mp7002SysTimingGen.description: Selects if the unit provides system timing. none(1) - does not provide Timing Generator primary(2) - unit is primary Timing Generator for the shelf. secondary(3) - unit is secondary Timig Generator for the shelf. Only 1 unit in the shelf can the primary or secondary timing generator. All other must be none.

mp7002DCCConfigurationTable.name: mp7002DCCConfigurationTable
mp7002DCCConfigurationTable.description: The GDC DCC Configuration table. These are Diagnostic Channel configuration options.

mp7002DCCConfigurationEntry.name: mp7002DCCConfigurationEntry
mp7002DCCConfigurationEntry.description: The GDC Diagnostic Configuration table entry.

mp7002DCCConfigurationIndex.name: mp7002DCCConfigurationIndex
mp7002DCCConfigurationIndex.description: Index value into the DCC Configuration table.

mp7002Bandwidth.name: mp7002Bandwidth
mp7002Bandwidth.description: Bandwidth to use: 8 kbps - bit 7 only 56 kbps - bits 0 - 6 64 kbps - all 8 bits

mp7002HighwayAssignTable.name: mp7002HighwayAssignTable
mp7002HighwayAssignTable.description: The GDC System Configuration table. These are unit options at the system level.

mp7002HighwayAssignEntry.name: mp7002HighwayAssignEntry
mp7002HighwayAssignEntry.description: The GDC E1 Highway Assign table entry.

mp7002HighwayAssignIndex.name: mp7002HighwayAssignIndex
mp7002HighwayAssignIndex.description: Index value into the Highway Assignment table.

mp7002TimeSlotBundle.name: mp7002TimeSlotBundle
mp7002TimeSlotBundle.description: Index for the bundle being assigned. A time slot bundle can be assigned to 1 or 2 of the 4 backplane highways. Bundle 1 is asigned in the Aggregate starting at Time Slot 1. Bundle 2 starts at the next available Time Slot. If only one bundle is needed, it must be bundle 1. The execute object should be sent only after acknowlegement of al assignment PDUs.

mp7002StartTimeSlot.name: mp7002StartTimeSlot
mp7002StartTimeSlot.description: Starting time slot of the bundle. If only 1 bundle is being assigned, or the first of 2 is being assigned, it must start at 1. The second of 2 must start at the next available time slot after the first bundle.

mp7002NumberOfTimeSlots.name: mp7002NumberOfTimeSlots
mp7002NumberOfTimeSlots.description: Number of time slots assigned to the bundle.

mp7002BundleDestination.name: mp7002BundleDestination
mp7002BundleDestination.description: Defines the destination of the bundle.

mp7002ExecuteAssign.name: mp7002ExecuteAssign
mp7002ExecuteAssign.description: Causes the MP7002 to execute configuration of the assigned highway configuration. This object should be sent in a separate PDU after acknowlegement of the assign PDU(s) has been recieved.

mp7002DiagTable.name: mp7002DiagTable
mp7002DiagTable.description: The GDC E1 Diagnostics table. Information in the entries of this table support diagnostics testing via loopbacks. Diagnostics are only supported when mp7002InterfaceType is set to niu(2). This table applies to the Network Interface only.

mp7002DiagEntry.name: mp7002DiagEntry
mp7002DiagEntry.description: The GDC E1 Diagnostics table entry.

mp7002DiagIndex.name: mp7002DiagIndex
mp7002DiagIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002TestPattern.name: mp7002TestPattern
mp7002TestPattern.description: Test pattern for tests that use the pattern generator. The value of this object is used when mp7002DiagConfig.unitTest(5) or mp7002DiagConfig.patGenOn(6) is selected. NOT SUPPORTED BY THE MP7002.

mp7002DiagConfig.name: mp7002DiagConfig
mp7002DiagConfig.description: Selects the test to run. noLoop(1) ends the test. Interoperates with mp7002TestPattern. When unitTest(2) or patGenOn(3) is selected, the pattern in mp7002TestPattern is used. payloadLoopback(4) and lineLoopback(5) are only valid when the unit is configured for a Network Side interface. localTest(6) is only valid when the unit is configured for a Drop Side interface.

mp7002TestLimit.name: mp7002TestLimit
mp7002TestLimit.description: Selects the duration to run a diagnostic test. The value(1) noLimit signifies that the test should run indefinitely until explicitly terminated. Default value: testTime10Mins(1)

mp7002TestExecutionStatus.name: mp7002TestExecutionStatus
mp7002TestExecutionStatus.description: This variable reports the status of a test. notInTest(1) indicates a test is not running. testInProgress(2) indicates that a test is currently running. testCompleted(4) indicates that a test has run and is completed. testCompletedNotInTest(5) indicates that a test has completed and it is no longer in test.

mp7002TestExceptions.name: mp7002TestExceptions
mp7002TestExceptions.description: Indicates exceptions that have occurred that may affect interpretation of the test results. The value of this object is a sum. This sum initially take the value zero. Then, for each exception, the value associated with the exception is added to the sum. The exception values are: value exception 1 a timed test was preempted so the result cannot be viewed in relation to the test duration 2 the results overflowed so the result cannot be viewed as an absolute value 4 the test was performed while synchronization could not be performed so the result may not be accurate.

mp7002TestResults.name: mp7002TestResults
mp7002TestResults.description: The results of the last diagnostic test. This can be the current test running or the last completed test. Note that the interpretation of these results may be affected by the value of the mp7002TestExceptions object. Not supported by MP7002 since no pattern generating tests are supported.

mp7002ResetTestResults.name: mp7002ResetTestResults
mp7002ResetTestResults.description: Resets the diagnostic error count. Not supported by MP7002 since no pattern generating tests are supported.

mp7002NearEndCurrent15MinEntry.name: mp7002NearEndCurrent15MinEntry
mp7002NearEndCurrent15MinEntry.description: An entry in the mp7002 NearEnd Current table.

mp7002NearEndCurrent15MinIndex.name: mp7002NearEndCurrent15MinIndex
mp7002NearEndCurrent15MinIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002NearEndIntervalEntry.name: mp7002NearEndIntervalEntry
mp7002NearEndIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the E1 Interval table.

mp7002NearEndIntervalIndex.name: mp7002NearEndIntervalIndex
mp7002NearEndIntervalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002NearEndIntervalNumber.name: mp7002NearEndIntervalNumber
mp7002NearEndIntervalNumber.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by an E1 interface in one of the previous 16, individual 15 minute, intervals.

mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrTable.name: mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrTable
mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrTable.description: The E1 Current24Hr table. 4 hour interval.

mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrEntry.name: mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrEntry
mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrEntry.description: An entry in the E1 Total table.

mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrIndex.name: mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrIndex
mp7002NearEndCurrent24HrIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002NearEndRecent24HrTable.name: mp7002NearEndRecent24HrTable
mp7002NearEndRecent24HrTable.description: The E1 Recent24Hr table. 4 hour interval.

mp7002NearEndRecent24HrEntry.name: mp7002NearEndRecent24HrEntry
mp7002NearEndRecent24HrEntry.description: An entry in the E1 Total table.

mp7002NearEndRecent24HrIndex.name: mp7002NearEndRecent24HrIndex
mp7002NearEndRecent24HrIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinEntry.name: mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinEntry
mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinEntry.description: An entry in the mp7002FarEnd Current 15 Minute table.

mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinIndex.name: mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinIndex
mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinStat.name: mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinStat
mp7002FarEndCurrent15MinStat.description: Returns a bitwise map of the far end interface in one of the previous 16, individual 15 minute, intervals. 1.7 f/u 1.6 f/u 1.5 f/u 1.4 f/u 1.3 f/u 1.2 2^9 ES . 1.0 2^7 2.7 f/u 2.6 2^6 . 2.0 2^0 3.7 f/u 3.6 f/u 3.5 f/u 3.4 f/u 3.3 f/u 3.2 2^9 SES . 3.0 2^7 4.7 f/u 4.6 2^6 SES . 4.0 2^0 5.7 f/u 5.6 f/u 5.5 f/u 5.4 f/u 5.3 f/u 5.2 Counter Overflow (>65535) BBE 5.1 2^15 5.0 2^14 6.7 f/u 6.6 2^13 BBE . 6.0 2^7 7.7 f/u 7.6 2^6 BBE . 7.0 2^0 8.7 f/u 8.6 f/u 8.5 f/u 8.4 f/u 8.3 f/u 8.2 2^9 UAS . 8.0 2^7 9.7 f/u 9.6 2^6 UAS . 9.0 2^0

mp7002FarEndIntervalEntry.name: mp7002FarEndIntervalEntry
mp7002FarEndIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the Interval table.

mp7002FarEndIntervalIndex.name: mp7002FarEndIntervalIndex
mp7002FarEndIntervalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002FarEndIntervalNumber.name: mp7002FarEndIntervalNumber
mp7002FarEndIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 16, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 16 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 16 intervals are valid).

mp7002FarEndIntervalStat.name: mp7002FarEndIntervalStat
mp7002FarEndIntervalStat.description: Returns a bitwise map of statistics for the far end interface in the current 15 minute interval. 1.7 f/u 1.6 f/u 1.5 f/u 1.4 f/u 1.3 f/u 1.2 2^9 ES . 1.0 2^7 2.7 f/u 2.6 2^6 . 2.0 2^0 3.7 f/u 3.6 f/u 3.5 f/u 3.4 f/u 3.3 f/u 3.2 2^9 SES . 3.0 2^7 4.7 f/u 4.6 2^6 SES . 4.0 2^0 5.7 f/u 5.6 f/u 5.5 f/u 5.4 f/u 5.3 f/u 5.2 Counter Overflow (>65535) BBE 5.1 2^15 5.0 2^14 6.7 f/u 6.6 2^13 BBE . 6.0 2^7 7.7 f/u 7.6 2^6 BBE . 7.0 2^0 8.7 f/u 8.6 f/u 8.5 f/u 8.4 f/u 8.3 f/u 8.2 2^9 UAS . 8.0 2^7 9.7 f/u 9.6 2^6 UAS . 9.0 2^0

mp7002CurrentFarEnd24HrEntry.name: mp7002CurrentFarEnd24HrEntry
mp7002CurrentFarEnd24HrEntry.description: An entry in the Current 24 Hr table.

mp7002CurrentFarEnd24HrIndex.name: mp7002CurrentFarEnd24HrIndex
mp7002CurrentFarEnd24HrIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002RecentFarEnd24HrEntry.name: mp7002RecentFarEnd24HrEntry
mp7002RecentFarEnd24HrEntry.description: An entry in the Recent 24 Hr table.

mp7002RecentFarEnd24HrIndex.name: mp7002RecentFarEnd24HrIndex
mp7002RecentFarEnd24HrIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002UnavailableTimeRegTable.name: mp7002UnavailableTimeRegTable
mp7002UnavailableTimeRegTable.description: The mp7002 Near End Unavailable Time Register table.

mp7002UnavailableTimeRegEntry.name: mp7002UnavailableTimeRegEntry
mp7002UnavailableTimeRegEntry.description: An entry in the Unavailable Time Register table.

mp7002UnavailableTimeRegIndex.name: mp7002UnavailableTimeRegIndex
mp7002UnavailableTimeRegIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002UnavailableTimeRegNumber.name: mp7002UnavailableTimeRegNumber
mp7002UnavailableTimeRegNumber.description: A number between 1 and 6, where the number is the number of the Unavailable Time Register.

mp7002UnavailableTimeRegStart.name: mp7002UnavailableTimeRegStart
mp7002UnavailableTimeRegStart.description: Start time of one of the Unavailable Time Registers.

mp7002UnavailableTimeRegStop.name: mp7002UnavailableTimeRegStop
mp7002UnavailableTimeRegStop.description: Stop time of one of the Unavailable Time Registers.

mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegTable.name: mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegTable
mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegTable.description: The mp7002 Unavailable Time Register table.

mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegEntry.name: mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegEntry
mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegEntry.description: An entry in the Unavailable Time Register table.

mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegIndex.name: mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegIndex
mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. This has the form of a SCinstance which defines the slot, line, drop, and interface. Interface can be Network or, when supported, E1X.

mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegNumber.name: mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegNumber
mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegNumber.description: A number between 1 and 6, where the number is the number of the Unavailable Time Register.

mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegStart.name: mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegStart
mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegStart.description: Start time of one of the Unavailable Time Registers.

mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegStop.name: mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegStop
mp7002FarEndUnavailableTimeRegStop.description: Stop time of one of the Unavailable Time Registers.

mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigTable.name: mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigTable
mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigTable.description: The mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigTable contains entries that configure alarm reporting. The structure of the table is such that alarm configuration is supported on a unit and interface basis, and then on an alarm type basis within the interface. For simplicity sake alarms, be they unit or interface related, are represented in one table.

mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigEntry.name: mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigEntry
mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the MP7002 Alarm Configuration table.

mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigIndex.name: mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigIndex
mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigIdentifier.name: mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigIdentifier
mp7002NearEndAlarmConfigIdentifier.description: The unique alarm identifier assigned to this alarm type. The format of this identifier is an OBJECT IDENTIFIER that has the following format: {iso(1) org(3) dod(6) internet(1) private(4) enterprises(1) gdc(498) xxx(x) alarm(z) yyy(y) where xxx(x) is the administratively assigned family object identifier (z) is the object identifier for alarms in the family defined MIB and yyy(y) is the administratively assigned alarm type identifier for this alarm.

mp7002NearEndAlarmCountWindow.name: mp7002NearEndAlarmCountWindow
mp7002NearEndAlarmCountWindow.description: This variable sets/reads the alarm window. This window is used with the alarm threshold to determine how long the alarm should be active before reporting. Default: disabled(1)

mp7002NearEndAlarmCountThreshold.name: mp7002NearEndAlarmCountThreshold
mp7002NearEndAlarmCountThreshold.description: This function sets/reads the alarm threshold criteria. This threshold is used along with the the alarm window to determine the number of instances in a given time frame for an alarm to occur before the alarm is considered active. Default: thresGT1(1)

mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigTable.name: mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigTable
mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigTable.description: The mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigTable contains entries that configure alarm reporting. The structure of the table is such that alarm configuration is supported on a unit and interface basis, and then on an alarm type basis within the interface. For simplicity sake alarms, be they unit or interface related, are represented in one table.

mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigEntry.name: mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigEntry
mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the MP7002 Alarm Configuration table.

mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigIndex.name: mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigIndex
mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigIdentifier.name: mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigIdentifier
mp7002FarEndAlarmConfigIdentifier.description: The unique alarm identifier assigned to this alarm type. The format of this identifier is an OBJECT IDENTIFIER that has the following format: {iso(1) org(3) dod(6) internet(1) private(4) enterprises(1) gdc(498) xxx(x) alarm(z) yyy(y) where xxx(x) is the administratively assigned family object identifier (z) is the object identifier for alarms in the family defined MIB and yyy(y) is the administratively assigned alarm type identifier for this alarm.

mp7002FarEndAlarmCountWindow.name: mp7002FarEndAlarmCountWindow
mp7002FarEndAlarmCountWindow.description: This variable sets/reads the alarm window. This window is used with the alarm threshold to determine how long the alarm should be active before reporting. Default: disabled(1)

mp7002FarEndAlarmCountThreshold.name: mp7002FarEndAlarmCountThreshold
mp7002FarEndAlarmCountThreshold.description: This function sets/reads the alarm threshold criteria. This threshold is used along with the the alarm window to determine the number of instances in a given time frame for an alarm to occur before the alarm is considered active. Default: thresGT1(1)

mp7002LocalAlarmConfigTable.name: mp7002LocalAlarmConfigTable
mp7002LocalAlarmConfigTable.description: The mp7002LocalAlarmConfigTable contains entries that configure alarm reporting. The structure of the table is such that alarm configuration is supported on a unit and interface basis, and then on an alarm type basis within the interface. For simplicity sake alarms, be they unit or interface related, are represented in one table.

mp7002LocalAlarmConfigEntry.name: mp7002LocalAlarmConfigEntry
mp7002LocalAlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Local Alarm Configuration table.

mp7002LocalAlarmConfigIndex.name: mp7002LocalAlarmConfigIndex
mp7002LocalAlarmConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

mp7002UASNE.name: mp7002UASNE
mp7002UASNE.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.
